@NODE conts "Contents of this package"
@prev main
@next feats

PACKAGE:
  DasModPlayer              - Program itself
  DasModPlayer,info         - Program icon
  DMODPAPPICON.info         - Application icon used by DMODP
  MOONLIGHT.TXT             - Moonlight Sonata info
  DASModPlayer.guide        - Documentation in AmigaGuide format
  libs/das.library          - Library needed by DMODP
  s/das-cfgfile.config      - Example Configuration file
  lists/list.default        - Default list for INITLIST tooltype
    

@ENDNODE
@NODE feats "Features list"
@NEXT gads
@PREV conts
		
D.A.S ModulePlayer Features list V.1.47 (not complete)

- File adding to program list:
    Multi/singlefile(s) through filerequester
    Whole directories through FR/application icon/window * NEW *
    Program files through FR/application icon/window

- Packers supported
    XPK libraries fully supported
    Powerpacker files through XPK master library
    LHA archives (external packer needed) Thanx Stefan Boberg
        Multiple files can be extracted from single archive
- Module types supported
    PT/NT/FLT (no other at this time, sorry)
- Fast ram relocation
- Commodity hotkey popup/hide
- Highly intelligent program list 
- Autoplay opt
- Automatic default list file loading on startup
- Hide window (iconify)
- Both the CIA and the VBlank interrupts by your choice
...
....
...... (Not every little but useful opt listed in here)

@ENDNODE

@NODE gads "Gadget Information for D.A.SModPlayer"
@prev feats
@next toolts
			
Load/SaveList 	
   Load throws you with a filerequester where you should
   select list-file to load.
   This can also be accomplished by just using "ADD" or throwing
   files icon to appwindow/icon
			
   SaveList throws you with a filerequester from where
   you are supposed to select/create new file to
   where your current module list is to be saved.

   You can compress list files using xpk library based packers.
   Do not compress list files using lha!


Add
   Hits you with a FileReq asking you to select a module
   to add to the module list. Multiselect supported.
   Whole directory loading supported. Just don't
   select any files only the drawer. ---> ZAZAMMM... the whole
   directory is being scanned and added to list. 

Del
   Deletes selected module or first module in list.

Exchg
   Swaps two modules with each other. First press
   Exchg then select first module and then the other.
				
Clear
   Clears the whole current list

Rep +/-
   Increase/decrease module's repetition count.
   Note: this is real repeat count so that count 3 in here
   means that module will be played 4 times.
   Rep (checkboxgad) overrides these values.

Play
   Loads/start playing module selected, or first
   module in list if none selected.

Stops
   As expected this one will terminate current play.

Prev
   Loads/start playing previous module.

Next
   Loads/starts playing next module in list.

<<
   Rewind - gadget. Goes one pattern backwards in module.

>>
   Fwd - gadget. Adds currently playing pattern count by one.

||
   Pauses the play, pressing this one again will continue

Info
   Shows a window containing instrument info about module
   There is also some info about location of samples and song
   and their respective sizes, Compression factor also found here.
   CF is always 0 on lha files.

Hide
   Closes the main window and maintains only the ApplicationIcon.
   If the appicon was not created then the hide option will be
   disabled. By double clicking the appicon you may bring 
   the main window back to life. 
   
   Same can be accomplished using hotkey combination
	

Prefs	- Jumps to prefs window

- Alloc channels Switch
   If you want to allocate channels using audio.device
   you should enable this option


- Preset vals	Switch
   If you enable this option and change tempo/speed settings 
   for a module then those values are presetted next time you
   play that module.


- Locate mod >fast
   Read section: MODULE RELOCATION TO FASTRAM


- LHA e/x fullpath 
   If your lha packet includes file with paths (not only file name)
   and you have used lha option x (or e without -x0) for extracting,
   then this option  instructs ModPlayer to use full path when loading 
   extracted file to memory. 
   Example: You have lha packet with a file audio/modules/mod.anthrax
   Normally you would put to 'lha opts' string following "e -x0 >NIL:"
   then the lha should extract the file to tempdir:mod.anthrax
   but if you have used 'lha opts' "x >NIL:" then lha would extract file
   to tempdir:audio/modules/mod.anthrax and if you DON'T have the
   'lha e/x fullpath' option enabled then player would try to read the
   file from tempdir:mod.Anthrax and not as it should be read tempdir:
   audio/modules/mod.Anthrax. (You got it right?)

   It is quite easy to just put lha opts = "e -x0 -N >NIL:" and let the
   'LHA e/x fullpath' gadget be disabled then the modules will be
   extracted to tempdir without any paths and everything goes just fine. :)


- Extr first in lha
   In enabled state this instructs player to just load first file
   from lha packet and ignore the rest. In disabled state this 
   tells the player to show every file in packet and play them
   accordingly. Check 'lha discard' gadget also.


-Autoplay
   When enabled causes the player to play automatically 
   module when you add it. If you do multiselect or load lha file
   with multiple files then last of them is played (not the first, 
   which would seem logical! But Hey ! who says this program 
   should be logical :) )

- Play mode 
   Lets you select of different playing modes. Selfexplanatory.
   Play all random is not doing actually anything (sorry!)


- Int type
   Interrupt type selection (CIA/VBLANK)
   If vblank is used PT command $F(>32) (Tempo set) is ignored.
   With CIA interrupt this works quite fine.

- Def list dir
   Write a default directory for list files.


- Def module dir
   Write a default directory for modules


- PT DMA WAIT	
   This is dma wait cycle amount for Protracker moduleplayer.
   Handle with care. If you change this one and start
   experiencing strange noises in near vicinity, try changing
   this back to what it was. I read somewhere that in fast
   machines like A3000/A4000 this should be set something like
   >1200-2000 



- Modpatt/listpatt
   Selection patterns for lists and mods. These are feeded to FileRequester.
   If nothing in here then FileRequester won't have Pattern gadget attached 
   in to it.


- Quit
   Closes the preferences window


- Save Prefs
   Saves preferences to S:DAS-CFGFILE.config.



@ENDNODE
@NODE toolts "Tooltype support for D.A.SModulePlayer"
@prev gads
@next packs


TOOLTYPES:

   When starting from workbench you can do certain initial procedures
   by setting Tooltypes in icon:
   <tooltype>=OFF  ; turns option off, same as not using it at all.

   INITHIDE=ON   
    Just pops up appicon. No window presented
    doubleclick in appicon causes the window popup

   INITINFO=ON   
    opens info window immediately after start

   INITLIST=ON   
    Loads a list named 'list.default' when starting the player

   OPENONPUBSCREEN=ON  
    opens windows in a PUBLICSCREEN (if any present)
    instead of WBENCHSCREEN.

   APPICONNAME=<path+name> 
    icons name which you want to use as appicon.

   CX_PRIORITY=<-127...127> Commodities priority

   CX_POPUP=ON/OFF should we use popup keys or not

   CX_POPKEY=ctrl lalt p
    Or something similar (ctrl lalt p = default)

   NOCOMMODITY=ON/OFF   When on, no commodity is used for player.


@ENDNODE



@NODE packs "Packer support"
@prev toolts
@next lists

COMPRESSORS SUPPORTED:

Powerpacker	
    Through powerpacker.library AND xpkmaster.library
	So you will need xpkmaster.library for powerpacker files!!!!

Xpk crunchers 
    through xpkmaster.library + appropriate xpk????.library


LHA PACKET HANDLING

   Open the prefs window, there you will find three new gadgets.
   Lha path = Path to your lha packer + lha itself (dh0:packers/lha/lha)
   Lha opts = options commands feeded to lha. YOU MUST ADD >NIL: TO THIS
   LINE. This is good 'opts' line --->  e -x0 -N >NIL: 
   temp dir = Temporary dir where lha packet should be temporarely
   extracted. Files extracted to here will be removed after loading.
   I will add 'keep unpacked lha'-option so that you don't have to 
   unpack constantly the same file over and over again.


   LHA discard = discard pattern to feed to lha packer. This one is
   used when 'extr first in lha' is disabled and player reads all
   files from lha packet. If you set this gadget forexample ~(#?read#?)
   then all files in lha with string 'read' will _not_ be added to list.



RANDOMID:
    When you add a lha packet to program list then player makes a random
    id code for that certain lha base and uses same id for files
    that are in the lha. If you load several previously saved lists
    at same time then this causes some distortion in list handling.
    Player won't crash your amiga or anything like that but when
    you remove one base several other files will be deleted also.

    So don't load same list twice!



@ENDNODE

@NODE lists "Program list"
@next fastram
@prev lists

Program list in DASModPlayer differs somewhat from other moduleplayers
lists. For instance there is one file type in the list which cannot be
played, they just hang in there. These items are called "lha bases".

LHA BASES:

Lha bases are different from other files in list that they have "< >"
in start and end of name. When such a file is encountered when playing list
they are simply skipped. 

When you have such a lha base in list it usually has archived file(s)
attached to it. if you remove lha base file then all its attached files
are also removed. If you remove all attached files then base file is also
removed.


HANDLING:

You can add/remove files to/from list. You can clear the whole list
and you can swap two items in list using "EXCHG" gadget. 

List is saved using "SAVE LIST" gadget. You can load these lists either
using "LOAD LIST" gadget or selecting them from FileRequester (ADD)
or just throwing their icons to player window or application icon.


@ENDNODE

@NODE fastram "FAST RAM Relocation"
@prev lists
@next rests


MODULE RELOCATION TO FASTRAM:

   You can switch option 'Relocate >FAST' on from prefs.    
   By enabling this option, the whole module will be loaded
   to fast ram and then sliced to Songdata and samples. Samples are
   then moved to chip memory one by one. After this player will
   try to relocate songdata to different part of Fastram, if
   this succeeds original module will be deallocated, if it doesn't
   succeed then player will unfortunately consume considerably 
   your fast memory resources, but still it is able to play the module.

   If there is not enough continuous FAST RAM then player will try
   to load the whole module to CHIP without asking user.
	
   Above mentioned Fastram relocation is just a first Phase of the
   Relocation implementation. I _may_ do a second phase which acts
   like Smartplay which takes only a certain amount of your CHIP
   and keeps most of the samples in fastram, copying them to chip as
   needed. Phase 2 takes quite a lot of CPU resources though. :(..

@ENDNODE
@NODE rests "Restrictions, system needed"
@prev fastram
@next apps

WHAT YOU NEED:


You will need operating system V37++
    At the present time I am doing this assembly on V40 kickstart
    so there might be some gadget outlook problems in KS2.04,
    due that commodore decided to change the Listview gadgets appearance.
    It should look same on every machine, but mainly 'cos I screwed up
    and used little too big listview size in KS2.04 it may look
    somewhat different. Sorry

You might need Powerpacker and xpk.... libraries.
    If you are going to use modules packed with xpk/powerpacker libraries
    then you will need respective libraries.

YOU WILL NEED das.library in your libs: drawer


WHAT YOU SHOULD **NOT** DO:    
    
Don't compress list files with lha. 
Don't compress files with xpk/pp and then stuff'em to lha packet. 
    Multiple packings are not supported.

Don't compress config file.


@ENDNODE
@NODE apps "Application implementation"
@prev rests
@next contact
This player supports few neat features presented in V36/37 such as:

Application window:
    You can just throw modules icons to players window and they are
    loaded as you had selected them using filerequester.    

Application icon:
    Same as application window.

    If you want to use the icon named DMODAPPICON as your application
    icon for DasModplayer you should keep it in a same drawer as 
    DasModPlayer itself, otherwise DMODP will use default project icon.
    If you don't like the way DMODPAPPICON looks, then just draw another
    one and rename it as 'DMODPAPPICON'
    You may also use the APPICONNAME=<> tooltype and define there
    the icon you want to use.




@ENDNODE
